#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="mn88"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn88:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 88 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 88 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: Bāhitikasutta → bāhitiyasuttaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "mn88:0.2"
msgid "Bāhitikasutta "
msgstr "The Imported Cloth "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, sc1
msgctxt "mn88:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn88:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2
msgctxt "mn88:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi. "
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Sāvatthī for alms. "

msgctxt "mn88:2.2"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena pubbārāmo migāramātupāsādo tenupasaṅkami divāvihārāya. "
msgstr "He wandered for alms in Sāvatthī. After the meal, on his return from alms-round, he went to the Eastern Monastery, the stilt longhouse of Migāra’s mother, for the day’s meditation. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3
msgctxt "mn88:3.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena rājā pasenadi kosalo ekapuṇḍarīkaṃ nāgaṃ abhiruhitvā sāvatthiyā niyyāti divā divassa. "
msgstr "Now at that time King Pasenadi of Kosala mounted the Single Lotus Elephant and drove out from Sāvatthī in the middle of the day. "

msgctxt "mn88:3.2"
msgid "Addasā kho rājā pasenadi kosalo āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ. "
msgstr "He saw Ānanda coming off in the distance "

msgctxt "mn88:3.3"
msgid "Disvāna sirivaḍḍhaṃ mahāmattaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "and said to the minister Sirivaḍḍha, "

msgctxt "mn88:3.4"
msgid "“āyasmā no eso, samma sirivaḍḍha, ānando”ti. "
msgstr "“My dear Sirivaḍḍha, isn’t that Venerable Ānanda?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn88:3.5"
msgid "“Evaṃ, mahārāja, āyasmā eso ānando”ti. "
msgstr "“Indeed it is, great king.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4, pts-vp-pli2.113, sc2
msgctxt "mn88:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo aññataraṃ purisaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then King Pasenadi addressed a man, "

msgctxt "mn88:4.2"
msgid "“ehi tvaṃ, ambho purisa, yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā mama vacanena āyasmato ānandassa pāde sirasā vandāhi: "
msgstr "“Please, mister, go to Venerable Ānanda, and in my name bow with your head to his feet. Say to him: "

msgctxt "mn88:4.3"
msgid "‘rājā, bhante, pasenadi kosalo āyasmato ānandassa pāde sirasā vandatī’ti; "
msgstr "‘Sir, King Pasenadi of Kosala bows with his head at your feet.’ "

msgctxt "mn88:4.4"
msgid "evañca vadehi: "
msgstr "And then say: "

msgctxt "mn88:4.5"
msgid "‘sace kira, bhante, āyasmato ānandassa na kiñci accāyikaṃ karaṇīyaṃ, āgametu kira, bhante, āyasmā ānando muhuttaṃ anukampaṃ upādāyā’”ti. "
msgstr "‘Sir, if you have no urgent business, please wait a moment out of compassion.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya5
msgctxt "mn88:5.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, devā”ti kho so puriso rañño pasenadissa kosalassa paṭissutvā yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho so puriso āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "“Yes, Your Majesty,” that man replied. He did as the king asked. "

msgctxt "mn88:5.2"
msgid "“rājā, bhante, pasenadi kosalo āyasmato ānandassa pāde sirasā vandati; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn88:5.3"
msgid "evañca vadeti: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn88:5.4"
msgid "‘sace kira, bhante, āyasmato ānandassa na kiñci accāyikaṃ karaṇīyaṃ, āgametu kira, bhante, āyasmā ānando muhuttaṃ anukampaṃ upādāyā’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya6
msgctxt "mn88:6.1"
msgid "Adhivāsesi kho āyasmā ānando tuṇhībhāvena. "
msgstr "Ānanda consented in silence. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "mn88:6.2"
msgid "Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo yāvatikā nāgassa bhūmi nāgena gantvā nāgā paccorohitvā pattikova yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho rājā pasenadi kosalo āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then King Pasenadi rode on the elephant as far as the terrain allowed, then descended and approached Ānanda on foot. He bowed, stood to one side, and said to Ānanda, "

msgctxt "mn88:6.3"
msgid "“sace, bhante, āyasmato ānandassa na kiñci accāyikaṃ karaṇīyaṃ, sādhu, bhante, āyasmā ānando yena aciravatiyā nadiyā tīraṃ tenupasaṅkamatu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, if you have no urgent business, it would be nice of you to go to the bank of the Aciravatī river out of compassion.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya7
msgctxt "mn88:7.1"
msgid "Adhivāsesi kho āyasmā ānando tuṇhībhāvena. "
msgstr "Ānanda consented in silence. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "mn88:7.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena aciravatiyā nadiyā tīraṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle paññatte āsane nisīdi. "
msgstr "He went to the river bank and sat at the root of a certain tree on a seat spread out. "

msgctxt "mn88:7.3"
msgid "Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo yāvatikā nāgassa bhūmi nāgena gantvā nāgā paccorohitvā pattikova yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho rājā pasenadi kosalo āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then King Pasenadi rode on the elephant as far as the terrain allowed, then descended and approached Ānanda on foot. He bowed, stood to one side, and said to Ānanda, "

msgctxt "mn88:7.4"
msgid "“idha, bhante, āyasmā ānando hatthatthare nisīdatū”ti. "
msgstr "“Here, Venerable Ānanda, sit on this elephant rug.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn88:7.5"
msgid "“Alaṃ, mahārāja. "
msgstr "“Enough, great king, "

msgctxt "mn88:7.6"
msgid "Nisīda tvaṃ; "
msgstr "you sit on it. "

msgctxt "mn88:7.7"
msgid "nisinno ahaṃ sake āsane”ti. "
msgstr "I’m sitting on my own seat.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya8
msgctxt "mn88:8.1"
msgid "Nisīdi kho rājā pasenadi kosalo paññatte āsane. "
msgstr "So the king sat down on the seat spread out, "

msgctxt "mn88:8.2"
msgid "Nisajja kho rājā pasenadi kosalo āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "and said, "

#. VAR: brāhmaṇehī”ti → brāhmaṇehi viññūhīti (si, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn88:8.3"
msgid "“kiṃ nu kho, bhante ānanda, so bhagavā tathārūpaṃ kāyasamācāraṃ samācareyya, yvāssa kāyasamācāro opārambho samaṇehi brāhmaṇehī”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, might the Buddha engage in the sort of behavior—by way of body, speech, or mind—that is faulted by ascetics and brahmins?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn88:8.4"
msgid "“Na kho, mahārāja, so bhagavā tathārūpaṃ kāyasamācāraṃ samācareyya, yvāssa kāyasamācāro opārambho samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhī”ti. "
msgstr "“No, great king, the Buddha would not engage in the sort of behavior that is faulted by sensible ascetics and brahmins.” "

#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.114, sc5
msgctxt "mn88:8.5"
msgid "“Kiṃ pana, bhante ānanda, so bhagavā tathārūpaṃ vacīsamācāraṃ … pe … "
msgstr " "

#. VAR: brāhmaṇehī”ti → brāhmaṇehi viññūhīti (si, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn88:8.6"
msgid "manosamācāraṃ samācareyya, yvāssa manosamācāro opārambho samaṇehi brāhmaṇehī”ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn88:8.7"
msgid "“Na kho, mahārāja, so bhagavā tathārūpaṃ manosamācāraṃ samācareyya, yvāssa manosamācāro opārambho samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhī”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya9, sc6
msgctxt "mn88:9.1"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante. "
msgstr "“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing! "

msgctxt "mn88:9.2"
msgid "Yañhi mayaṃ, bhante, nāsakkhimhā pañhena paripūretuṃ taṃ, bhante, āyasmatā ānandena pañhassa veyyākaraṇena paripūritaṃ. "
msgstr "For I couldn’t fully express the question, but Ānanda’s answer completed it for me. "

msgctxt "mn88:9.3"
msgid "Ye te, bhante, bālā abyattā ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā paresaṃ vaṇṇaṃ vā avaṇṇaṃ vā bhāsanti, na mayaṃ taṃ sārato paccāgacchāma; "
msgstr "I don’t believe that praise or criticism of others spoken by incompetent fools, without examining or scrutinizing, is the most important thing. "

# NOTE: In certain contexts, (eg MN 38) paccagacchati seems to have its literal sense of “fall back on” in the sense of “revert to more primitive practices or beliefs”. However, this passage shows that the meaning is more idiomatic than this. We could, of course, read it differently in the different contexts. However it seems unlikely that it would have a more abstract meaning in a simple ordinary language context as here, and a more concrete, literal meaning in a philosophical context.
#. VAR: viyattā → byattā (bj) | byattā viyattā (s1-3) | vyattā (pts1)
#. VAR: pana → ye ca kho (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn88:9.4"
msgid "ye pana te, bhante, paṇḍitā viyattā medhāvino anuvicca pariyogāhetvā paresaṃ vaṇṇaṃ vā avaṇṇaṃ vā bhāsanti, mayaṃ taṃ sārato paccāgacchāma. "
msgstr "Rather, I believe that praise or criticism of others spoken by competent and intelligent people after examining and scrutinizing is the most important thing. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya10, sc7
msgctxt "mn88:10.1"
msgid "Katamo pana, bhante ānanda, kāyasamācāro opārambho samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhī”ti? "
msgstr "But sir, what kind of bodily behavior is faulted by sensible ascetics and brahmins?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn88:10.2"
msgid "“Yo kho, mahārāja, kāyasamācāro akusalo”. "
msgstr "“Unskillful behavior.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "mn88:10.3"
msgid "“Katamo pana, bhante, kāyasamācāro akusalo”? "
msgstr "“But what kind of bodily behavior is unskillful?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn88:10.4"
msgid "“Yo kho, mahārāja, kāyasamācāro sāvajjo”. "
msgstr "“Blameworthy behavior.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "mn88:10.5"
msgid "“Katamo pana, bhante, kāyasamācāro sāvajjo”? "
msgstr "“But what kind of bodily behavior is blameworthy?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: sabyābajjho → sabyāpajjho (bj, s1-3, km) | savyāpajjho (pts1) | sabyāpajjo (mr)
msgctxt "mn88:10.6"
msgid "“Yo kho, mahārāja, kāyasamācāro sabyābajjho”. "
msgstr "“Hurtful behavior.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "mn88:10.7"
msgid "“Katamo pana, bhante, kāyasamācāro sabyābajjho”? "
msgstr "“But what kind of bodily behavior is hurtful?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn88:10.8"
msgid "“Yo kho, mahārāja, kāyasamācāro dukkhavipāko”. "
msgstr "“Behavior that results in suffering.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "mn88:10.9"
msgid "“Katamo pana, bhante, kāyasamācāro dukkhavipāko”? "
msgstr "“But what kind of bodily behavior results in suffering?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn88:10.10"
msgid "“Yo kho, mahārāja, kāyasamācāro attabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati. "
msgstr "“Bodily behavior that leads to hurting yourself, hurting others, and hurting both, "

msgctxt "mn88:10.11"
msgid "Tassa akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti; "
msgstr "and which makes unskillful qualities grow while skillful qualities decline. "

msgctxt "mn88:10.12"
msgid "evarūpo kho, mahārāja, kāyasamācāro opārambho samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhī”ti. "
msgstr "That kind of bodily behavior is faulted by sensible ascetics and brahmins.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya11, sc12
msgctxt "mn88:11.1"
msgid "“Katamo pana, bhante ānanda, vacīsamācāro … pe … "
msgstr "“But what kind of verbal behavior … "

msgctxt "mn88:11.2"
msgid "manosamācāro opārambho samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhī”ti? "
msgstr "mental behavior is faulted by sensible ascetics and brahmins?” … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn88:11.3"
msgid "“Yo kho, mahārāja, manosamācāro akusalo”. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.115, sc13
msgctxt "mn88:11.4"
msgid "“Katamo pana, bhante, manosamācāro akusalo”? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn88:11.5"
msgid "“Yo kho, mahārāja, manosamācāro sāvajjo”. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "mn88:11.6"
msgid "“Katamo pana, bhante, manosamācāro sāvajjo”? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn88:11.7"
msgid "“Yo kho, mahārāja, manosamācāro sabyābajjho”. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya12, sc15
msgctxt "mn88:12.1"
msgid "“Katamo pana, bhante, manosamācāro sabyābajjho”? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn88:12.2"
msgid "“Yo kho, mahārāja, manosamācāro dukkhavipāko”. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "mn88:12.3"
msgid "“Katamo pana, bhante, manosamācāro dukkhavipāko”? "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn88:12.4"
msgid "“Yo kho, mahārāja, manosamācāro attabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati. "
msgstr "“Mental behavior that leads to hurting yourself, hurting others, and hurting both, "

msgctxt "mn88:12.5"
msgid "Tassa akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti; "
msgstr "and which makes unskillful qualities grow while skillful qualities decline. "

msgctxt "mn88:12.6"
msgid "evarūpo kho, mahārāja, manosamācāro opārambho samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhī”ti. "
msgstr "That kind of mental behavior is faulted by sensible ascetics and brahmins.” "

# NOTE: BB’s translation here is odd “only the abandoning of all unskillful states”. Elsewhere the same idiom appears (MN 15, MN 70, AN 10.55) where it rather has the sense: “the abandoning of all these (specifically aforementioned) unskillful states”
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya13, sc17
msgctxt "mn88:13.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu kho, bhante ānanda, so bhagavā sabbesaṃyeva akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānaṃ vaṇṇetī”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, does the Buddha praise giving up all these unskillful things?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn88:13.2"
msgid "“Sabbākusaladhammapahīno kho, mahārāja, tathāgato kusaladhammasamannāgato”ti. "
msgstr "“Great king, the Realized One has given up all unskillful things and possesses skillful things.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya14, sc18
msgctxt "mn88:14.1"
msgid "“Katamo pana, bhante ānanda, kāyasamācāro anopārambho samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhī”ti? "
msgstr "“But sir, what kind of bodily behavior is not faulted by sensible ascetics and brahmins?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn88:14.2"
msgid "“Yo kho, mahārāja, kāyasamācāro kusalo”. "
msgstr "“Skillful behavior.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "mn88:14.3"
msgid "“Katamo pana, bhante, kāyasamācāro kusalo”? "
msgstr "“But what kind of bodily behavior is skillful?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn88:14.4"
msgid "“Yo kho, mahārāja, kāyasamācāro anavajjo”. "
msgstr "“Blameless behavior.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20
msgctxt "mn88:14.5"
msgid "“Katamo pana, bhante, kāyasamācāro anavajjo”? "
msgstr "“But what kind of bodily behavior is blameless?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn88:14.6"
msgid "“Yo kho, mahārāja, kāyasamācāro abyābajjho”. "
msgstr "“Pleasing behavior.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21
msgctxt "mn88:14.7"
msgid "“Katamo pana, bhante, kāyasamācāro abyābajjho”? "
msgstr "“But what kind of bodily behavior is pleasing?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn88:14.8"
msgid "“Yo kho, mahārāja, kāyasamācāro sukhavipāko”. "
msgstr "“Behavior that results in happiness.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc22
msgctxt "mn88:14.9"
msgid "“Katamo pana, bhante, kāyasamācāro sukhavipāko”? "
msgstr "“But what kind of bodily behavior results in happiness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn88:14.10"
msgid "“Yo kho, mahārāja, kāyasamācāro nevattabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, na parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, na ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati. "
msgstr "“Bodily behavior that leads to pleasing yourself, pleasing others, and pleasing both, "

msgctxt "mn88:14.11"
msgid "Tassa akusalā dhammā parihāyanti, kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti. "
msgstr "and which makes unskillful qualities decline while skillful qualities grow. "

msgctxt "mn88:14.12"
msgid "Evarūpo kho, mahārāja, kāyasamācāro anopārambho samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhī”ti. "
msgstr "That kind of bodily behavior is not faulted by sensible ascetics and brahmins.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya15, sc23
msgctxt "mn88:15.1"
msgid "“Katamo pana, bhante ānanda, vacīsamācāro … pe … "
msgstr "“But what kind of verbal behavior … "

