msgctxt "mn88:16.7"
msgid "Tassa akusalā dhammā parihāyanti, kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti. "
msgstr "and which makes unskillful qualities decline while skillful qualities grow. "

msgctxt "mn88:16.8"
msgid "Evarūpo kho, mahārāja, manosamācāro anopārambho samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhī”ti. "
msgstr "That kind of mental behavior is not faulted by sensible ascetics and brahmins.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya17, sc28
msgctxt "mn88:17.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ pana, bhante ānanda, so bhagavā sabbesaṃyeva kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadaṃ vaṇṇetī”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, does the Buddha praise embracing all these skillful things?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn88:17.2"
msgid "“Sabbākusaladhammapahīno kho, mahārāja, tathāgato kusaladhammasamannāgato”ti. "
msgstr "“Great king, the Realized One has given up all unskillful things and possesses skillful things.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya18, sc29
msgctxt "mn88:18.1"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante. "
msgstr "“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing! "

msgctxt "mn88:18.2"
msgid "Yāva subhāsitañcidaṃ, bhante, āyasmatā ānandena. "
msgstr "How well this was said by Venerable Ānanda! "

msgctxt "mn88:18.3"
msgid "Iminā ca mayaṃ, bhante, āyasmato ānandassa subhāsitena attamanābhiraddhā. "
msgstr "I’m delighted and satisfied with what you’ve expressed so well. "

msgctxt "mn88:18.4"
msgid "Evaṃ attamanābhiraddhā ca mayaṃ, bhante, āyasmato ānandassa subhāsitena. "
msgstr "So much so that "

msgctxt "mn88:18.5"
msgid "Sace, bhante, āyasmato ānandassa hatthiratanaṃ kappeyya, hatthiratanampi mayaṃ āyasmato ānandassa dadeyyāma. "
msgstr "if an elephant treasure was suitable for you, I would give you one. "

msgctxt "mn88:18.6"
msgid "Sace, bhante, āyasmato ānandassa assaratanaṃ kappeyya, assaratanampi mayaṃ āyasmato ānandassa dadeyyāma. "
msgstr "If a horse treasure was suitable for you, I would give you one. "

msgctxt "mn88:18.7"
msgid "Sace, bhante, āyasmato ānandassa gāmavaraṃ kappeyya, gāmavarampi mayaṃ āyasmato ānandassa dadeyyāma. "
msgstr "If a prize village was suitable for you, I would give you one. "

#. VAR: mayampetaṃ → mayampetaṃ taṃ (si) | mayampanetaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn88:18.8"
msgid "Api ca, bhante, mayampetaṃ jānāma: "
msgstr "But, sir, I know that "

msgctxt "mn88:18.9"
msgid "‘netaṃ āyasmato ānandassa kappatī’ti. "
msgstr "these things are not suitable for you. "

# NOTE: The Chinese parallel at MA 214 supports the reading chatta, i.e. umbrella 繖https://suttacentral.net/lzh/ma214/49.238. BB translates the commentary when he says “sixteen hands”. But this is impossible as it stands. 16x8 spans is only big enough for one robe, maybe a little more (Cf. pacittiya 92, where the maximum robe is 9x6 spans) But Ananda is supposed to make a whole set of three robes from this. Either a different measure is in use, or else the mention of “three” is a later addition, and originally it was meant for one robe. However the Chinese also has “three”. Regarding the rendering of bahitika, I accept the commentary’s explanation that it means “imported”. It is an unusual term, apparently only occurring here, and, as international trade was still somewhat rare in the time of the Buddha—even cloth from Kasi was regarded as special—this gives a better reason for why it is so special. This being so, there is no reason to accept the PTS dict’s explanation as “that which keeps out”, i.e. cloak. A royal cloak would likely be highly fashioned and decorated, and difficult to adapt as a monk’s robe. It makes more sense if it is simply fine imported cloth.
#. VAR: vatthanāḷiyā → chattanāḷiyā (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn88:18.10"
msgid "Ayaṃ me, bhante, bāhitikā raññā māgadhena ajātasattunā vedehiputtena vatthanāḷiyā pakkhipitvā pahitā soḷasasamā āyāmena, aṭṭhasamā vitthārena. "
msgstr "This imported cloth was sent to me by King Ajātasattu Vedehiputta of Magadha packed in a parasol case. It’s exactly sixteen measures long and eight wide. "

msgctxt "mn88:18.11"
msgid "Taṃ, bhante, āyasmā ānando paṭiggaṇhātu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti. "
msgstr "May Venerable Ānanda please accept it out of compassion.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn88:18.12"
msgid "“Alaṃ, mahārāja, paripuṇṇaṃ me ticīvaran”ti. "
msgstr "“Enough, great king. My three robes are complete.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya19, pts-vp-pli2.117, sc30
msgctxt "mn88:19.1"
msgid "“Ayaṃ, bhante, aciravatī nadī diṭṭhā āyasmatā ceva ānandena amhehi ca. "
msgstr "“Sir, we have both seen this river Aciravatī "

msgctxt "mn88:19.2"
msgid "Yadā uparipabbate mahāmegho abhippavuṭṭho hoti, athāyaṃ aciravatī nadī ubhato kūlāni saṃvissandantī gacchati; "
msgstr "when it has rained heavily in the mountains, and the river overflows both its banks. "

msgctxt "mn88:19.3"
msgid "evameva kho, bhante, āyasmā ānando imāya bāhitikāya attano ticīvaraṃ karissati. "
msgstr "In the same way, Venerable Ānanda can make a set of three robes for himself from this imported cloak. "

msgctxt "mn88:19.4"
msgid "Yaṃ panāyasmato ānandassa purāṇaṃ ticīvaraṃ taṃ sabrahmacārīhi saṃvibhajissati. "
msgstr "And you can share your old robes with your fellow monks. "

msgctxt "mn88:19.5"
msgid "Evāyaṃ amhākaṃ dakkhiṇā saṃvissandantī maññe gamissati. "
msgstr "In this way my religious donation will come to overflow, it seems to me. "

msgctxt "mn88:19.6"
msgid "Paṭiggaṇhātu, bhante, āyasmā ānando bāhitikan”ti. "
msgstr "Please accept the imported cloth.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya20
msgctxt "mn88:20.1"
msgid "Paṭiggahesi kho āyasmā ānando bāhitikaṃ. "
msgstr "So Ānanda accepted it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc31
msgctxt "mn88:20.2"
msgid "Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then King Pasenadi said to him, "

msgctxt "mn88:20.3"
msgid "“handa ca dāni mayaṃ, bhante ānanda, gacchāma; "
msgstr "“Well, now, sir, I must go. "

msgctxt "mn88:20.4"
msgid "bahukiccā mayaṃ bahukaraṇīyā”ti. "
msgstr "I have many duties, and much to do.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn88:20.5"
msgid "“Yassadāni tvaṃ, mahārāja, kālaṃ maññasī”ti. "
msgstr "“Please, great king, go at your convenience.” "

msgctxt "mn88:20.6"
msgid "Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo āyasmato ānandassa bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi. "
msgstr "Then King Pasenadi approved and agreed with what Ānanda said. He got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled Ānanda, keeping him on his right, before leaving. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya21, sc32
msgctxt "mn88:21.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando acirapakkantassa rañño pasenadissa kosalassa yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
msgstr "Soon after he left, Ānanda went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, "

msgctxt "mn88:21.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando yāvatako ahosi raññā pasenadinā kosalena saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ bhagavato ārocesi. "
msgstr "and told him what had happened. "

msgctxt "mn88:21.3"
msgid "Tañca bāhitikaṃ bhagavato pādāsi. "
msgstr "He presented the cloth to the Buddha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya22
msgctxt "mn88:22.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to the mendicants, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn88:22.2"
msgid "“lābhā, bhikkhave, rañño pasenadissa kosalassa, suladdhalābhā, bhikkhave, rañño pasenadissa kosalassa; "
msgstr "“Mendicants, King Pasenadi is lucky, so very lucky, "

msgctxt "mn88:22.3"
msgid "yaṃ rājā pasenadi kosalo labhati ānandaṃ dassanāya, labhati payirupāsanāyā”ti. "
msgstr "to get to see Ānanda and pay homage to him.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc33
msgctxt "mn88:22.4"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "mn88:22.5"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti. "
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn88:22.6"
msgid "Bāhitikasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

